7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 619, L.D. 960, “An Act Facilitating the
10 Discharge of Hospitalized Patients to Nursing Facilities”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Allow the Placement of Hospitalized Patients in Nursing Facilities in
13 Alternative Locations Under Certain Circumstances'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Alternative nursing facility locations. Resolved: That the Department
16 of Health and Human Services shall amend its rules in Chapter 101: MaineCare Benefits
17 Manual, Chapter II, Section 67, Nursing Facility Services, to allow for the placement of a
18 MaineCare member, when the member is being discharged from a hospital to a nursing
19 facility placement, in a nursing facility that is greater than 60 miles from the member's
20 residence under the following conditions.
21 1. For placements that are beyond 60 miles from the member's residence but not more
22 than 100 miles from the member's residence, the hospital must have attempted to find a
23 placement that is within a 60-mile radius of the member's residence and those efforts,
24 including refusals by facilities, must be documented.
25 2. For placements beyond 60 miles of the member's residence, the member must be
26 provided with information, including written materials and contact information, about the
27 long-term care ombudsman program in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section
28 5107-A for use by the member if the member determines, at any point, that a closer
29 placement is desired.
30 3. For placements beyond 100 miles from the member's residence, the member or
31 member's guardian must consent to the placement.'
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
